About your father-in-law's case?

389
00:33:26,110 --> 00:33:27,270
They may feel embarrassed.

390
00:33:27,730 --> 00:33:28,890
Okay.

391
00:33:28,970 --> 00:33:29,570
By the way,

392
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:32,960
well,

393
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:35,020
I want to talk about the commission.

394
00:33:35,050 --> 00:33:36,720
I'm still angry with the airlines.

395
00:33:36,740 --> 00:33:37,430
Another time.

396
00:33:38,950 --> 00:33:39,880
That's too much.

397
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:42,630
None of your business.

398
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:35,989
Grandpa is so much stronger than you are.

399
00:34:36,010 --> 00:34:37,110
You can wake up.

400
00:34:37,750 --> 00:34:38,960
He can too.

401
00:34:42,500 --> 00:34:43,370
What about the calligraphy training center?

402
00:34:44,409 --> 00:34:45,120
I forgot to tell you.

403
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:46,139
We moved.

404
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:49,210
We moved?

405
00:34:51,340 --> 00:34:52,480
Is that something you can forget about?

406
00:34:53,370 --> 00:34:54,409
Your daughter is getting married.

407
00:34:55,050 --> 00:34:56,389
That's why you are taking the house back?

408
00:34:56,590 --> 00:34:57,450
Yes.

409
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:59,230
I'm sorry for the last-minute request.

410
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:01,750
I remember you told me

411
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:03,630
that you didn't have any kids.

412
00:35:03,700 --> 00:35:05,230
That's why you're buying houses everywhere

413
00:35:05,650 --> 00:35:06,180
to plan

414
00:35:06,180 --> 00:35:07,740
for your life when you are old.

415
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:09,930
Did I?

416
00:35:10,590 --> 00:35:11,450
When did I tell you that?

417
00:35:11,450 --> 00:35:13,800
1:30 p.m. on March 1st, 2014.

418
00:35:13,910 --> 00:35:15,050
How could you remember it so accurately?

419
00:35:15,350 --> 00:35:17,160
You asked me if I could pay

420
00:35:17,190 --> 00:35:18,500
for half a year's rent,

421
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:20,060
because you needed the revenue stream.

422
00:35:20,220 --> 00:35:21,630
And because it was my birthday that day,

423
00:35:21,650 --> 00:35:23,130
I paid a lot for it.

424
00:35:23,630 --> 00:35:24,910
So I remember it clearly.

425
00:35:25,860 --> 00:35:27,980
Happy birthday.

426
00:35:29,970 --> 00:35:31,650
Can you tell me the real reason?

427
00:35:35,510 --> 00:35:37,120
Your son and your father-in-law

428
00:35:37,170 --> 00:35:38,600
will not stay in the hospital forever, won't they?

429
00:35:39,490 --> 00:35:40,540
If they were moved back...

430
00:35:40,560 --> 00:35:41,690
You're worried that they may die in the house?

431
00:35:43,640 --> 00:35:45,230
No landlord accepts this?

432
00:35:51,250 --> 00:35:52,980
Or how about you buy one?

433
00:35:56,430 --> 00:35:58,030
So you spent all the compensation?

434
00:35:58,470 --> 00:36:00,120
Now we die if we want to

435
00:36:00,670 --> 00:36:01,840
and we'll die in our own home.

436
00:36:01,970 --> 00:36:02,770
No one would dare to badger us.

437
00:36:02,940 --> 00:36:04,090
Excuse me.

438
00:36:04,330 --> 00:36:05,850
Can you not say that word here?

439
00:36:06,220 --> 00:36:07,230
Or you can lower your voice.

440
00:36:07,830 --> 00:36:08,690
Sorry.

441
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:11,220
Please live a long life.

442
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:15,680
Besides, if grandpa

443
00:36:15,700 --> 00:36:17,200
wants to continue teaching calligraphy,

444
00:36:17,220 --> 00:36:19,010
there will be a place he can start anytime.

445
00:36:21,610 --> 00:36:22,570
You're right.

446
00:36:23,010 --> 00:36:24,590
You don't have to care about others anymore.

447
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:26,970
She's right.

448
00:36:34,850 --> 00:36:36,020
Can I go outside now?

449
00:36:37,230 --> 00:36:38,570
It's been almost two years.

450
00:36:39,060 --> 00:36:41,170
It's hard to say if your situation will maintain stability or not.

451
00:36:50,150 --> 00:36:51,020
Don't forget your crutches.

452
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:02,990
You really don't need your mother to accompany you?

453
00:37:14,060 --> 00:37:14,490
Doctor.

454
00:37:17,750 --> 00:37:18,420
Be brave.

455
00:37:18,740 --> 00:37:19,160
You can do this.

456
00:37:19,380 --> 00:37:19,970
Lend me 500 yuan.

457
00:37:26,990 --> 00:37:27,630
700.

458
00:37:56,030 --> 00:37:56,470
Okay.

459
00:38:07,700 --> 00:38:09,050
Is this the right place?

460
00:38:17,790 --> 00:38:18,910
Can you pull over here?

461
00:38:19,830 --> 00:38:20,200
Okay.

462
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:21,250
Okay.

463
00:38:21,770 --> 00:38:23,160
It's okay. I'll stop the meter.

464
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:24,330
Take your time.

465
00:39:54,210 --> 00:39:55,950
Pull over here. Thank you.

466
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:57,570
How much is this?

467
00:40:01,110 --> 00:40:01,980
Okay.

468
00:40:10,620 --> 00:40:11,070
Over there.

469
00:40:11,740 --> 00:40:12,350
What do you think?

470
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:15,440
It's a little complicated.

471
00:40:16,870 --> 00:40:17,600
It's either good

472
00:40:17,630 --> 00:40:18,450
or bad.

473
00:40:18,560 --> 00:40:19,720
What is so complicated?

474
00:40:21,180 --> 00:40:22,320
It's too different from what I expected just now.

475
00:40:22,740 --> 00:40:23,590
Don't ask for trouble.

476
00:40:28,030 --> 00:40:28,420
Mum.

477
00:40:29,620 --> 00:40:30,400
Someone's over there.

478
00:40:32,090 --> 00:40:32,830
Who? Where?

479
00:40:33,570 --> 00:40:33,980
There. That one.

480
00:40:34,680 --> 00:40:35,460
The one next door.

481
00:40:38,860 --> 00:40:39,770
It seems she's looking at me.

482
00:40:41,210 --> 00:40:42,010
No one's there.

483
00:40:43,150 --> 00:40:43,790
There she is.

484
00:40:44,830 --> 00:40:45,900
Don't be silly.

485
00:40:45,930 --> 00:40:46,460
Go inside.

486
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:47,130
You didn't see her?

487
00:40:48,030 --> 00:40:49,290
No, I didn't.

488
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:50,190
Oh no.

489
00:40:51,460 --> 00:40:52,460
You bought a house

490
00:40:52,460 --> 00:40:53,440
where an old woman died next door and couldn't rest in peace.

491
00:40:53,520 --> 00:40:54,120
And it cost you so much money.

492
00:40:54,140 --> 00:40:55,030
Who couldn't rest in peace?

493
00:40:58,800 --> 00:41:00,210
I'm sorry.

494
00:41:00,530 --> 00:41:02,110
I was just kidding with my son.

495
00:41:02,630 --> 00:41:03,100
Greet her.

496
00:41:04,230 --> 00:41:04,790
How?

497
00:41:05,510 --> 00:41:06,530
Granny Zeng Jiang.

498
00:41:06,550 --> 00:41:07,820
She's our neighbor.

499
00:41:08,630 --> 00:41:10,660
This is my son, Yiyong.

500
00:41:17,350 --> 00:41:19,150
My son Yiyong.

501
00:41:20,990 --> 00:41:22,320
